```json
{
  "type": "postgres",
  "host": "localhost",
  "port": 5432,
  "username": "postgres",
  "password": "password",
  "database": "chat_app_db",
  "synchronize": false,
  "logging": true,
  "entities": [
    "src/database/entities/**/*.ts"
  ],
  "migrations": [
    "src/database/migrations/**/*.ts"
  ],
  "subscribers": [
    "src/database/subscribers/**/*.ts"
  ],
  "seeds": [
    "src/database/seeds/**/*.ts"
  ],
  "cli": {
    "entitiesDir": "src/database/entities",
    "migrationsDir": "src/database/migrations",
    "subscribersDir": "src/database/subscribers"
  }
}
```
**Note**: When running within Docker, `host` will be the service name (`db`). This file is primarily for CLI commands. In `data-source.ts`, we'll use environment variables.